sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Kernel as Jupyter Kernel<br/>Internal IPC
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PyPI as PyPI Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GitHub as GitHub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Access to Jupyter Workbench

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>Path: /lab<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Router->>OAuth: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS 8443/TCP<br/>OpenShift Session
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OpenShift<br/>OAuth Token
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Authenticated Request<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP
    Jupyter->>Kernel: Execute Code<br/>IPC (Local Process)
    Kernel-->>Jupyter: Execution Result
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: Response
    OAuth-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Jupyter,S3: Flow 2: Workbench to S3 Storage

    Jupyter->>S3: Download Training Data<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>AWS IAM Credentials
    S3-->>Jupyter: Data Objects<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Jupyter->>S3: Upload Model Artifacts<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>AWS IAM Credentials
    S3-->>Jupyter: Upload Confirmation

    Note over Jupyter,PyPI: Flow 3: Package Installation

    User->>Jupyter: pip install {package}
    Jupyter->>PyPI: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.2+<br/>No Auth
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Python Package
    Jupyter-->>User: Installation Complete

    Note over Jupyter,GitHub: Flow 4: Git Operations

    User->>Jupyter: git clone {repo}
    Jupyter->>GitHub: HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>or SSH 22/TCP<br/>Git Credentials/SSH Key
    GitHub-->>Jupyter: Repository Contents
    Jupyter-->>User: Clone Complete

    Note over Jupyter,ModelReg: Flow 5: Model Registration

    Jupyter->>ModelReg: Register Trained Model<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP<br/>Service Mesh mTLS<br/>Bearer Token
    ModelReg-->>Jupyter: Model Version ID
    Jupyter-->>User: Registration Success

    Note over Jupyter,K8sAPI: Flow 6: Kubernetes API Access

    User->>Jupyter: oc get pods
    Jupyter->>K8sAPI: HTTPS 6443/TCP<br/>TLS 1.3<br/>Service Account Token
    K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: Pod List
    Jupyter-->>User: Display Results
